e1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4828x2716+0+583/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F94%2Fee1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4828x2716+0+583/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F94%2Fee1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4828x2716+0+583/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F94%2Fee1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4828x2716+0+583/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F94%2Fee1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4828x2716+0+583/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F94%2Fee1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4828x2716+0+583/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F94%2Fee1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4828x2716+0+583/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F94%2Fee1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/4828x2716+0+583/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F2a%2F94%2Fee1fda9540bd8caa7f9fa346c689%2Fme-michigan-elections-jpg-012.jpg" class="img" alt="A Trump and Harris sign side-by-side in a neighborhood on Oct. 3, 2024 in Hillsdale, Mich." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 A Trump and Harris sign side-by-side in a neighborhood on Oct. 3, 2024 in Hillsdale, Mich.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Sylvia Jarrus for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;NPR is visiting &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/09/16/g-s1-22212/election-harris-trump-swing-states"&gt;&lt;em&gt;six key swing states&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt; that will likely decide this year’s historic election. This week, Morning Edition is in Michigan to listen to voters about what matters to them and how that will affect their vote.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Michigan, a “blue wall” state, is part of Vice President Harris’ clearest path to the White House.&lt;/strong&gt; But the victory won’t be easy. Harris and former President Donald Trump remain in a close battle. Here are &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/06/nx-s1-5130163/michigan-2024-election-harris-trump"&gt;key factors that could decide&lt;/a&gt; which way Michigan swings:&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;ul class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;🗳️ &lt;strong&gt;Voters in the state care most about &lt;/strong&gt;the economy, abortion and immigration. Michigan enshrined abortion and reproductive health rights in its constitution two years ago.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🗳️&lt;strong&gt; Michigan has suffered for decades&lt;/strong&gt; from a decline in automobile manufacturing and high interest rates constricting the sale of cars.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;🗳️ &lt;strong&gt;Arab and Muslim voters largely supported &lt;/strong&gt;Biden in 2020, but have since felt alienated by how he has handled the Israel-Gaza war.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ul&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;Behind the story&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-25950" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 8307;         --source-height: 4673;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/8307x4673+0+433/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F44%2F6f%2F58acce1140d2a7a5aacdfd926dd9%2Fbeeri-edit-18.jpg" class="img" alt="One year after October 7th, a look at Kibbutz Beeri and how the survivors have moved forward after 102 Kibbutz members have been killed and 3 are still held hostage in Gaza." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 One year after October 7th, a look at Kibbutz Beeri and how the survivors have moved forward after 102 Kibbutz members have been killed and 3 are still held hostage in Gaza.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Maya Levin for NPR                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This essay was written by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/576543610/daniel-estrin"&gt;&lt;em&gt;&lt;u&gt;Daniel Estrin&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;em&gt;, NPR's international correspondent in Jerusalem.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“The day still keeps surprising us,”&lt;/strong&gt; my colleague Anas Baba in Gaza texted me last Oct. 7, close to midnight.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I was at a hospital in southern Israel. &lt;/strong&gt;The waiting room was full of parents in a daze, waiting for word about their children who had come under attack at an outdoor techno rave near the Gaza border. In Gaza, our producer Anas was taking photos of families fleeing their homes as Israeli airstrikes rained down.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;It was the deadliest day in Israeli history. It sparked the deadliest war in Palestinian history.&lt;/strong&gt; One year later, it has grown into a regional war. Every day keeps surprising us.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A year later, I find myself thinking about where the survivors and witnesses of this war draw strength.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;I think about Batya Ofir, &lt;/strong&gt;a woman my colleague Itay Stern and I met the other day at Kibbutz Be’eri, the Israeli village that suffered the greatest loss — 102 people there were killed. Her brother was killed along with his family. She felt survivor’s guilt, and she told us she asked herself &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/07/g-s1-25787/israel-october-7-kibbutz-beeri-hamas-attack-anniversary"&gt;whether she wanted to keep on living&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“I really thought about it. And then I decided that I wanted to continue to live,” &lt;/strong&gt;she said. Today, she is learning how to kayak in the sea to help her face her fears. “I do everything to give some meaning to life now that they're gone.”&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Our colleague Anas Baba in Gaza has been reporting for NPR in Gaza all year.&lt;/strong&gt; Again and again, he has videotaped bodies brought into the morgue after Israeli airstrikes. He always trains his camera on young children, sheltering near the morgue, standing alone and watching silently as bodies are laid out.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What gives him strength, he said, is collecting biscuits and fruit to give to the children he meets.&lt;/strong&gt; “I can help them survive,” he told me.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;He often meets a young girl named Habiba at the hospital in central Gaza.&lt;/strong&gt; She’s been colorblind since birth. One day, she told Anas she saw a man drowning with water coming out of his nose. It wasn't water; it was blood.&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;“This girl does not know the color of blood,” &lt;/strong&gt;Anas told me. “I wish all the children in Gaza were colorblind now.”&lt;br&gt;&lt;/p&gt;   &lt;h3 class="edTag"&gt;3 things to know before you go&lt;/h3&gt;   &lt;div id="resg-s1-26418" class="bucketwrap image large"&gt;             &lt;div     class="imagewrap has-source-dimensions"     data-crop-type=""     style="         --source-width: 5392;         --source-height: 3033;     " &gt;         &lt;picture&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/400/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/900/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/1200/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/1600/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/1800/quality/85/format/webp/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/webp" /&gt;             &lt;source srcset="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/400/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 400w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 800w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/900/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 900w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/1200/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 1200w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/1600/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 1600w, https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/1800/quality/85/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg 1800w" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg" sizes="(min-width: 1300px) 763px, (min-width: 1025px) calc(100vw - 496px), (min-width: 768px) calc(100vw - 171px), calc(100vw - 30px)" class="img" type="image/jpeg" /&gt;             &lt;img src="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/1100/quality/50/format/jpeg/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg" data-template="https://npr.brightspotcdn.com/dims3/default/strip/false/crop/5392x3033+0+280/resize/{width}/quality/{quality}/format/{format}/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fnpr-brightspot.s3.amazonaws.com%2F9a%2F65%2F7c57fbf944259274f9158efd7f63%2Fgettyimages-1925798281.jpg" class="img" alt="Merriam-Webster online has added 200 new words to its database." loading="lazy" /&gt;         &lt;/picture&gt; &lt;/div&gt; &lt;div class="credit-caption"&gt;     &lt;div class="caption-wrap"&gt;         &lt;div class="caption" aria-label="Image caption"&gt;             &lt;p&gt;                 Merriam-Webster online has added 200 new words to its database.                 &lt;b class="credit" aria-label="Image credit"&gt;                                          Photo illustration: Brandon Bell/Getty Images                                      &lt;/b&gt;                 &lt;b class="hide-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;             &lt;/p&gt;         &lt;/div&gt;               &lt;b class="toggle-caption"&gt;&lt;b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;&lt;/b&gt;     &lt;/div&gt;       &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;/div&gt;    &lt;ol class="edTag"&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Online dictionary Merriam-Webster.com, has updated its database&lt;/strong&gt; with 200 new words and phrases, &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/04/g-s1-26417/new-words-phrases-added-merriam-webster"&gt;including "touch grass" and "MAGA."&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;In 2023, Corey Widmer's car broke down in the middle of a busy intersection while he was on the way to get his car checked. &lt;/strong&gt;This is when his unsung heroes &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/04/nx-s1-5139437/good-news-kindness-stranger-car-help"&gt;helped him through the nightmarish situation&lt;/a&gt;. A man asking for money at a median helped him move the car to the side of the road. Men in another car helped him restart the stalled vehicle.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A crucial loan program designed to &lt;/strong&gt;help disaster victims will &lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/2024/10/04/nx-s1-5140667/hurricane-helene-loans-biden-kamala-harris-trump"&gt;run out of money within weeks&lt;/a&gt;, President Biden said in a letter sent to Congress on Friday. This comes at a time when Americans affected by Hurricane Helene urgently need relief.&lt;/li&gt;&lt;/ol&gt;       &lt;p&gt;&lt;em&gt;This newsletter was edited by &lt;/em&gt;&lt;a href="https://www.npr.org/people/g-s1-2467/obed-manuel"&gt;&lt;em&gt;Suzanne Nuyen.&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt; &lt;/div&gt;</description>
